# Google Sheets API Configuration
# For local development or Vercel deployment, choose ONE of the methods below:

# Method 1: Service Account JSON file (local development - RECOMMENDED)
# 1. Create a service account in Google Cloud Console
# 2. Download the JSON key file
# 3. Save it to: ~/.config/google-calendar/service-account.json
# 4. Share your Google Sheet with the service account email
# The API will automatically detect and use this file!

# Method 2: Service Account Environment Variables (Vercel/production)
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console > APIs & Services > Credentials
# 2. Create a Service Account and generate a JSON key
# 3. Share your Google Sheet with the service account email
# 4. Add these environment variables in Vercel:
# GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL=your-service-account@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com
# GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYourPrivateKey\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# Method 3: OAuth Access Token (simpler for quick setup)
# Note: Access tokens expire, this is mainly for development
# GOOGLE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_access_token
